  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the tandoor clay pot to 180 degrees Fahrenheit using sous-vide techniques.",
    "In a large bowl, combine broad beans, carrots, potatoes, onions, garlic, and celery.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together vegetable broth, olive oil, thyme, salt, and pepper.",
    "Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir until they are well combined.",
    "Transfer the stew mixture to the preheated tandoor clay pot.",
    "Cook the stew for 2 hours, or until the vegetables are tender.",
    "Stir the stew occasionally to prevent burning or sticking.",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with fresh herbs if desired.",
    "Let the stew cool completely before refrigerating or freezing.",
    "Reheat the stew to 165 degrees Fahrenheit before serving."
  ],
